data.enText: a piece of furniture in a dining room for putting food on before it is served, with drawers for storing knives, forks, etc.

tr: a piece of furniture that stands at the side of a dining room
a board that forms part of the side of a bed or crib
a removable board fitted on the side of a wagon to increase its capacity

value.def: A sideboard is a long cupboard which is about the same height as a table. Sideboards are usually kept in dining rooms to put plates and glasses in.
